						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">In <a href="https://twitter.com/nesdoug2/status/919227712157442049" class="postlink">this Tweet</a>, dougeff wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">what are people using discord for? I imagine its just a more annoying IRC chat, since people will be talking over each other.</div><br />Slack and Discord fit in a space somewhere between IRC and a forum. Here are some features that Discord has and IRC lacks:<br /><br /><ul><li>The server automatically logs text channels. A user can view messages sent to a channel while the user was offline without each user having to obtain a shell account on which to run ZNC.</li><li>Membership in a set of related text and voice channels is grouped, and the owner of such a group can sync permissions throughout the group by assigning roles to members.</li><li>Users can upload attachments to the server, and the client embeds previews of attachments and linked websites. Unlike with DCC, no port forwarding is required.</li><li>Users can add emojis as reactions to a message, and it counts how many users have added each reaction to a message. </li></ul><br />What IRC server and client extensions would allow all of the above?</div>

